 BY TIMOTHY AGBOR, OSOGBO Association of Local Government Chairmen of Nigeria, Osun State Chapter, on Friday, lauded the state governor, Gboyega Oyetola for completing the Olaiya flyover his administration embarked upon. To this end, the council chairmen appealed to the people of the state to reelect Oyetola for second term to enable him continue the good works he started. Speaking during the inspection of Olaiya flyover in Osogbo, the ALGON Chairman, Abiodun Idowu, expressed satisfaction over the completion of the flyover, saying that Oyetola would do more if given second chance. Idowu urged the people of the state to reciprocate the infrastructural transformation of the state by trooping out on July 16 to reelect Oyetola. “The entire council chairmen of Osun State appreciate Governor Adegboyega Oyetola for creating this initiative (flyiv) and for getting it fulfilled, not only fulfilling but fulfilling to time and to promise. So, we appreciate the efforts of Mr Governor at our level by coming to see things ourselves and to pronounce the appreciation to the world. “The flyover is marvellous, fantastic because people that are conversant with this place before can testify that something remarkable has been put on ground. It can also be described as innovation with an exception. “Osun people are highly appreciative and educated and know the value of structure. So, on July 16 the Osun people will do wonders positively in such way that Mr Governor will Know that people are appreciating his efforts,” he said. 